snippet.textDisplay: I have to say I agree with a good few of these sins Joker was just a cringefest, I just left the cinema wondering why I had such mixed feelings about it and concluded some of the scenes were brilliant but they never transitioned well. It ended up completely disjointed with cheap political ire thrown in and not in a way that would make you think of mental illness or as a link to the state of the MCs headspace just as bad editing. The plot was nonsensical and it relies way too much on the empathy of the viewer going into overdrive from cringing at the MC. I dont regret watching it and some parts make good short clips but I doubt I will ever  watch it again.
